The paper deals with the problem of minimal actuator placement in a linear control system, which is a topic related to control theory and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics and Automation) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of supermodular structure and approximation algorithms indicates a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
